  "prompt": "Will time travel be possible in future?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, time travel remains a theoretical concept rather than a practical reality. While there are various theories and discussions in the realm of physics, particularly in relation to Einstein's theory of relativity, that suggest time travel could be possible under certain conditions (e.g., wormholes, warp drives, and cosmic strings), no experimental evidence or technology currently supports the feasibility of such travel.\n\nThe concept of time travel often involves highly complex and speculative scenarios that would require advancements far beyond our current technological capabilities. Many physicists also point out potential paradoxes and challenges associated with time travel, such as causality issues (e.g., the grandfather paradox) and energy requirements.\n\nTherefore, while it is an intriguing and frequently discussed topic in both science and science fiction, time travel is not currently possible and remains an open question for future scientific exploration.",
